Uses of NSI in kdl.prox.nsi2.nsi
 

Classes in kdl.prox.nsi2.nsi that implement NSI
 class APSPNSI
          The All Pairs Shortest Path NSI stores the exact graph distance for all pairs of nodes.
 class DegreeNSI
          The Degree NSI labels each node with its degree.
 class DTZNSI
          The DTZ NSI, or distance-to-zone, computes a Zone NSI and then for each node, stores the shortest distance to each other zone.
 class GNPNSI
          The GNP NSI is based on the Global Network Positioning system proposed by Ng & Zhang in 2002.
 class LandmarksNSI
          The Landmarks NSI chooses a set of landmarks and stores the exact distance from every node to each landmark.
 class MatrixFactorizationNSI
          The Matrix Factorization NSI is based on techniques proposed by Mao & Saul in 2004.
 class SearchNSI
          The Search NSI uses a searching routine to provide distances.
 class ZoneNSI
          The Zone NSI works by assigning each node a label corresponding to one of k zones The zones are chosen by randomly flooding from k seed nodes until all nodes have been labeled.
